The psychology of bidding in excess: why spend more money?
Buyers are willing to spend more on auctions, to overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and researchers at the University of New York have been able to discover the neuro-economic bases of this known and apparently irrational behavior.
According to their study published in the journal Science men do not want to stay back in a race such as eBay auction, so they are available to pay even a higher price.
The research sought to trace the nervous pattern of this part of the nervous system through experimental astements.
One group of volunteers played the lot, the other group of players participated in an auction while using the functional magnetic resonance method (fMRI) examined the active areas of the brain of the participants in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win money, but in the auction game, in which the substantial element is to bid more than the other, the body striated under the cerebral cortex comes intensively into operation when you lose the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the mechanism of self-gratification of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to researchers, the rise of the price is explained by scanning the vehemently reaction of the striato body.
To support their theory, the economists of the research group conducted a financial follow-up investigation.
In this investigation, three groups have tendered against a partner under different conditions.
The control group reported on the actual value of the product in question and made their bets.
To another group besides this they promised that in the case of winning they will receive another $15 prize.
The third group would have received 15 dollars before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost the money in the event of a loss on the auction.
The difference between the two groups consisted in the fact that for one of them the win was emphasized, while for the other the loss.
By checking the hypothesis of the neurologists the members of the group that played - against the loss - were willing to make higher bets of the control group or - winning -
These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
In fact, these so far explained the phenomena encountered in auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurological image have helped to resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we have come to a third explanation - said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics of the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when do you contact your doctor?
Almost half a billion people in the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, in Hungary, chronic liver diseases are mentioned among the first causes of death.
In Hungary, the number of hepatitis sufferers amounts to one hundred thousand, of which only 7000 are treated: the reason is that many patients do not know how to be infected.
Hepatitis is the collective name of contagious liver disease caused by different viruses.
There are many similarities between symptoms, typical of hepatitis and jaundice, but their pathogenic agents and caused diseases differ from one another.
Hepatitis viruses are spread in two main forms depending on the pathogenic agent: hepatitis A and E through the food channel (e.g. water and food), hepatitis B, C, D and other blood viruses and organic fluids (sperm, vaginal losses, saliva).
For those travelling it is useful to immunize against A and B virus, against C there is no vaccine.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two-three weeks after eating infected foods, accompanied by general malaise, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After yellow spots are formed on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the dark urine, the healing takes place in two-three weeks.
A million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, which causes liver tumors and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason is, according to estimates, that only one in ten persons receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if it is not treated it can cause liver cirrhosis and tumors.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because pathogens subdolently destroy liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore, it is very important to prevent and carry out regular medical tests.
This disease is much more common than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
Today in the world the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
Since a routine laboratory examination also reveals that the disease is worth addressing the family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated by the organism, so ceases the infectious power and can be prevented the formation of tumors.
September 30 is the world day of hepatitis, organized for the first time in 2004 by disease associations worldwide.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the result of a recent investigation, religious faith functions as a sort of painkiller that made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
Scientists at Oxford University carried out an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God influences the feeling of pain, the British Telegraph reported.
Within the framework of the rather bizarre investigation, an electroshock was carried out with 12 Catholic believers and with as many atheists, while all observed a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
Based on the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for the control of pain.
The test is the first of a series of research in which, in addition to academics, scientists, philosophers and theologians of the University also take part.
The test was carried out exactly this way: a tool that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the experiment subject.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the Virgin Mary painted in the 17th century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with Leonardo da Vinci's hermellin painted in the 15th century.
The authors of the exam hoped that the image of the Virgin Mary would originate a sort of religious state among the believers, while Leonardo's painting was chosen because it did not differ too much from the other and they considered it to be a reassuring effect.
The subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this time period they received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while observing or painting on religious theme or the other.
Catholics reported that the vision of the Virgin Mary made them feel \"safe\" as if \"someone took care\" of them and \"they were calmed down and were pervaded by peace\"
Looking at the religious image, they realized 12% less pain than they had before them the work of Leonardo.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image with a strong effect even for atheists, but we must find the image suitable.
\"We must look for an image to which very positive feelings, like a mother or a father,\" said the psychologist.
Anglican Bishop Tom Wright was pleased with the result of the search.
“The practice of faith should change, and in many cases it manages to change our personality,” Wright added.
After the excellent results, only the question remains if the painting of a Madonna of Leonardo or another painter of the same caliber is presented to the believers, what effect could it have on the control of pain?
Would the vision of a virgin Mary of quality bring better results?
