National industrial sales prices in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, of 12.9% in comparison to August 2007 - reports the Hungarian Central Statistical Institute.
Export sales prices of the industry reported in July 2008 were higher than 1.1%, compared to the previous year fell by 3.9%
As a result of the variation in domestic and export prices the industrial costs of production were higher than 0.7% compared to the previous month and 3.2% compared to a year ago.
The prices of the previous month's reported domestic industrial sales increased by only 0.1%.
National sales prices in the manufacturing sector also rose to a minimum of 0.1%, compared to July.
The highest price increase in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe manufacturing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoe production with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastic and chemical raw materials has caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the product and chemical sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of instruments and electrical machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in woodworking (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the manufacturing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
