A decrease in prices occurred in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the manufacturing industry, the rate of price increases ranged from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total, prices in the manufacturing industry in the past year rose by 10.2%.
The prices of the electricity supply, gas, steam and water sector exceeded 18.7% of last year's prices.
In national sales among target groups in the sector, the largest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in the sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods prices have grown by 0.3%, in the energy and subsequent use sectors prices have not changed compared to those in the previous month.
