Listening to high-volume music for an extended period of time using portable musical devices such as Mp3 readers can cause permanent hearing injuries.
This is what the European Commission refers to, which in a statement issued in Brussels quotes the opinion of the newly identified Scientific Committee on Emerging Health Risks (Csseri) of the EU, published today.
